!!Ham Mesh Projects
[[Broadband-Hamnet]] (formerly called HSMM-Mesh) is a
[[Wireless Mesh Network]]
operated by the ham radio community with a focus on emergency communications.
The [[Northwest MESH Amateur Radio Networking|http://nw-mesh.wikidot.com/]]
maintains a list of helpful links.

!!Non-Ham Mesh Projects
* [[Waggle|http://www.rfidjournal.com/articles/view?12823]] - An [[IoT]] Platform by Scientists, for Scientists
* [[Quick Mesh Project|http://qmp.cat/Home]] - Level 3 routing based on [[BMX|http://bmx6.net/projects/bmx6]] fork of routing in [[OpenWrt|https://openwrt.org/]]
* [[Village Telco|http://villagetelco.org/]] - low-cost community telephone network called Mesh Potato
* [[Byzantium|http://project-byzantium.org/]] - wireless mesh networking for the Zombie apocalypse
* [[Serval Mesh|http://www.servalproject.org/]] - direct connections between cellular phones through their [[WiFi]] interfaces with [[Mesh Extender|https://github.com/servalproject/mesh-extender-builder]]
* [[SPAN|http://www.mitre.org/research/technology-transfer/open-source-software/smartphone-ad-hoc-networking-span]] - Smart Phone Ad-hoc Network
* [[Commotion Wireless|https://commotionwireless.net/]] - an open-source communication tool that uses mobile phones, computers, and other wireless devices
* [[Hyperboria|http://hyperboria.net/]] - a global decentralized network of "nodes" running [[Cjdns|https://wiki.projectmeshnet.org/Cjdns]] software as part of [[Project Meshnet|https://projectmeshnet.org/]]
* [[Nightwing|http://nightwing.lugro-mesh.org.ar/en/]] - allows the creation of fast deployment wireless networks
* [[Subnodes|http://subnod.es/]] - non-Internet Mesh Network on Raspberry Pi